# MUI Grid Component Usage

## Grid Component Import

In this project, we use the GridLegacy component instead of the standard Grid component from Material UI. Always use the following import pattern when working with Grid components:

```typescript
import { GridLegacy as Grid } from '@mui/material';
```

or include it in your existing MUI imports:

```typescript
import {
  // other imports
  GridLegacy as Grid,
  // other imports
} from '@mui/material';
```

## Proper Grid Usage

When using Grid components, follow this pattern:

```tsx
<Grid container spacing={3}>
  <Grid item xs={12} md={6}>
    {/* Your content */}
  </Grid>
  <Grid item xs={12} md={6}>
    {/* Your content */}
  </Grid>
</Grid>
```

## Common Properties

- `container`: Used on parent Grid elements to create a container
- `item`: Used on child Grid elements to create items
- `spacing`: Controls the spacing between grid items (used on container)
- `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`: Responsive breakpoints for different screen sizes

